law.text:
The Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene shall provide a statewide system:
To control rabies;
To grant authority to the public health veterinarian and the local health officer in matters pertaining to the disposition of animals that bite or otherwise expose rabies to an individual;
To assist local political subdivisions regarding the laboratory testing of rabid animals;
To treat each individual who is exposed or suspected of having been exposed to rabies; and
To distribute, in accordance with the conditions set by the Secretary of Agriculture, the biological products that are needed to prevent and treat rabies.
